--> IPv4 
	classfull addressing - huge wastage of addresses
	classless addressing - 
	IP addresses are 32 bit 
	
--> Classes
	Class A - 0 to 127
	Class B - 128 to 191
	Class C - 192 to 223
	Class D - 224 to 239
	Class E - 240 to 255

--> Masking concept
	An address in the blovk and the mask will create the beginning address.
	
--> Default mask for:-
	Class A - 255.0.0.0
	Class B - 255.255.0.0
	Class C - 255.255.255.0
	
--> Packet with loopback address will not reach the network


